==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-snub.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Transitive verb===
'''snub''' (snubbed, snubbing, snubs)

#To [[slight]], [[ignore]] or [[behave]] [[cold]]ly toward someone.
#To [[turn down]], [[dismiss]] or [[frustrate]] the [[plan]] of someone.
#''He '''snubbed''' my offer to help.''
#To [[stub out]] (a [[cigarette]] etc).
#To [[halt]] the movement of a [[rope]] etc by [[turning]] it about a [[cleat]] or [[bollard]] etc; to [[secure]] a [[vessel]] in this manner.

===Noun===
'''snub'''

#A [[deliberate]] [[affront]] or slight.
#:''I hope the people we couldn't invite don't see it as a '''snub'''.''
#A [[sudden]] checking of a [[cable]] or rope.

===Adjective===
'''snub'''
#[[Unusually]] [[short]].